      • getByExpression

        java.lang.Object getByExpression(java.lang.String expression)
        gets the value of a model property by evaluating the expression language of the underlying template system. Often a convenience method that calls evaluateContextExpression(String).
        Parameters:
        expression - an expression in the template system's native expression language;
        Returns:
        the evaluation product for expression, or null if the evaluation fails.

        the value of the property.

      • evaluateContextExpression

        java.lang.Object evaluateContextExpression(java.lang.String expression)
                                    throws ExpressionFailedException
        Evaluate context expression.
        Parameters:
        expression - text representing an evaluable expression for the underlying template system.
        Returns:
        the evaluated result of the expression.
        Throws:
        ExpressionFailedException - The template system failed to evaluate the expression and arrive at a result.
